A brainstorming session was held and a number of factors were identified as possible causes:
The model was “wrong” and predicted exposures were lower than expected, or
The model was “right” but the observed Swiss TPH exposure data were higher than expected because of:
Differences in the study population (healthy volunteers vs patients);
Differences between crushed tablets and intact tablets, number of tablets administered, or solubility saturation;
Differences in the meal composition;
Differences in bioavailability between adults and children; and/or
Differences in biological matrix (plasma vs dried blood spot).
